                    <p>The agency request is for two contingency funds: $100 million for security
                        assistance and $30 million for other foreign aid contingencies, principally
                        disaster relief needs. We recommend continuation of one fund to preserve
                        maximum Presidential flexibility. Our recommendation <pb facs="0215" n="189"
                            xml:id="pg_189"/> of $50 million reflects a judgment that the Congress
                        is unlikely to appropriate even that much, as recent experience
                        indicates.</p>
